After setting the status changes define:

| Field            | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       |
|------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| User permissions | It allows you to determine which USER OR USER GROUP is authorized to change the status; <img width="" src="https://docs.eos-solutions.it/Images/PR000531-0/8DataSecurity(1).png"><br>  It is also possible to establish that, when a change of status implies that another user needs to complete missing data (e.g. the administration user must enter data regarding payment methods on a registry):   - an email must be sent to that user - the user receives a notification on his rolecenter (see [EDS Notification Text List](https://helpbc.eos-solutions.it/main.aspx?lang=en&content=ENU_DataSecurity_EDSNotifications.html)). NB The notification sending is not currently enabled for User groups. Clicking "All Users" button it is possible to proceed by providing the permissions massively to all and then eliminating from the list who should not have them.   |
| Mandatory Fields | They allow you to establish the fields that need to be filled in to be able to change the status <img width="" src="https://docs.eos-solutions.it/Images/PR000531-0/11DataSecurity(1).png"><br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 |
| Functions        | On each status change you can apply predefined functions to check business rules or define mandatory fields or fields rules.  <img width="" src="https://docs.eos-solutions.it/Images/PR000531-0/12DataSecurity(1).png"><br> N-Functions are avaliable. You can set custom functions (see the [available functions](https://helpbc.eos-solutions.it/main.aspx?lang=en&content=ENU_DataSecurity_EDSFunctions.html) ). It is useful, for example, when you need a customer to be blocked when in NEW status, (nobody can use/modify it), until it passes in CERTIFIED status. The user, in order to create documents concerning that customer, must first bring it in a Certified status (filling in all the information requested).                                                                                                                                     |
